        <div class="featurette">
          <div class="page-header"><h1 class="featurette-heading" id="artist">The Artist. <span class="muted">Concentrate on Performing.</span></h1></div>
          <p class="lead"><strong>PR, lobbying or industry experience is irrelevant on 100 Motels.</strong> Music decides, there is no other consideration. So make recordings you like, get them out into the commons and then practice your performance. </p>
          <p class="lead">After you sign up add a music or video playlist to your profile. Look through local events for a support slot, or organizer profiles if you're looking to tour a particular location. To register your interest just click the request button on the event/organizer profile page. The organizer will receive a private message with your media and contact email. You can track and cancel all requests in your user account. </p>
          <p class="lead">If you receive an offer to tour from an Organizer you need to agree a sales target to cover your costs, once that's done you can expect the Organizer to handle everything else. </p>
        </div>
